WHAT IS KISS? WHAT IS "KISEKAE"?

  Kisekae is Japanese for "changing clothes". It's a popular play for
little girls. They are given "kisekae ningyou (dolls for changing
clothes)" and play changing clothes of the dolls. And, girls' manga
magazines sometimes provide paper dolls and clothes for kisekae.

  Kiss (KISekae Set system) simulates kisekae with paper dolls on your
computer. The Kiss system consists of a Kiss program and Kiss data. A
Kiss data is a set of pictures. The Kiss program displays the
character with several clothes (dress, shirt, socks, shoes, hat etc)
and allows you to changing the clothes by manipulating them.

