WHAT FILES DO I NEED? HOW CAN I GET KISS DATA?

  To play with Kiss you need a Kiss program and Kiss data. Kiss
programs are so far available for the following platforms:

file name	platform		conformance(*)
---------	--------		--------------
KISS237 .LZH	NEC PC-9801		KISS/GS3?
KISS68D .LZH	Sharp X68000		KISS/GS1?
KSTW237 .LZH	Fujitsu FM-TOWNS	KISS/GS3?
KIS237_5.LZH	PC/AT PC-DOS, DOS/V	KISS/GS3
WKISS056.LZH	Microsoft Windows 3.1	KISS/GS4?
KissMac4.LZH	Macintosh		KISS/GS3?
xkis200c.tar.gz	X11R4 or later		KISS/GS4
AmiKiss11.lha	AmigaDOS		KISS/GS1?

(*)Description about KISS/GS is not done yet.

  Choose an appropriate one for your computer.
  The older version of Kiss for DOS/V did not work on plain PC-DOS
(MS-DOS) and you needed a TSR named "japanit" unless you have DOS/V
